cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CE 

This paper discusses the economic issues related to P2P technology and its impact on ISPs, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a cooperative profit-distribution model based on game theory (cs.GT) and discusses the fairness and feasibility of the proposed mechanism (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper considers the overall efficiency of the network system (cs.SI) and the economic implications for content providers (cs.CE).
